      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "text": ">>> import binaryninja as bn\n>>> bv = bn.load(\"/bin/cat\")\n<BinaryView: '/bin/cat', start 0x100000000, len 0x14178>\n>>> bv.functions\n[<func: x86@0x1337>, ..., <func: x86@0x16be>]\n>>> func = bv.get_function_at(0x1337)\n>>> func.llil\n<LowLevelILFunction: x86@0x1337>\n>>> func.mlil.source_function\n<func: x86@0x1337>\n>>> hlil = func.hlil\n>>> for func in bv.functions:\n..:   # Entrypoint for function-level analysis\n..:   for bb in func.hlil:\n..:     # Entrypoint for block-level analysis\n..:     for inst in bb:\n..:       # Entrypoint for instruction-level analysis\n..:       inst\n",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": ">>> import binaryninja as bn\n>>> bv = bn.load(\"/bin/cat\")\n<BinaryView: '/bin/cat', start 0x100000000, len 0x14178>\n>>> bv.functions\n[<func: x86@0x1337>, ..., <func: x86@0x16be>]\n>>> func = bv.get_function_at(0x1337)\n>>> func.llil\n<LowLevelILFunction: x86@0x1337>\n>>> func.mlil.source_function\n<func: x86@0x1337>\n>>> hlil = func.hlil\n>>> for func in bv.functions:\n..:   # Entrypoint for function-level analysis\n..:   for bb in func.hlil:\n..:     # Entrypoint for block-level analysis\n..:     for inst in bb:\n..:       # Entrypoint for instruction-level analysis\n..:       inst\n",
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "baseline": 451
